Section 1: Q&A; Pairs

Example 1.1

User

What is a transformer model?
AI Response

A transformer is a deep learning architecture using self-attention mechanisms that process all tokens in
parallel, enabling efficient NLP. GPT and BERT are transformer-based models.

Example 1.2

User

What is a decision tree?
AI Response

A decision tree splits data by feature values at internal nodes, with leaves representing predictions. They are
interpretable but prone to overfitting without pruning.

Example 1.3

User

What is an RNN?
AI Response

A Recurrent Neural Network processes sequential data with loops allowing information to persist. LSTMs and
GRUs are variants that address the vanishing gradient problem.

Example 1.4

User

What is a GAN?
AI Response

A Generative Adversarial Network pits a generator (creates fake data) against a discriminator (identifies
fakes), training each other until the generator produces realistic data.

Example 1.5

User

What is regularization?
AI Response

Regularization adds a penalty to the loss function to discourage model complexity. L1 promotes sparsity; L2
penalizes large weights. Both reduce overfitting.

Example 1.6

User

What is RLHF?
AI Response

Reinforcement Learning from Human Feedback trains a reward model on human preference data, then uses
RL (PPO) to fine-tune an LLM to produce outputs humans prefer.

Example 1.7

User

What is the vanishing gradient problem?
AI Response



In deep networks, gradients shrink exponentially during backpropagation, preventing early layers from
learning. Solutions include ReLU activations, residual connections, and LSTMs.

Example 1.8

User

What is overfitting?
AI Response

Overfitting occurs when a model learns training data too well—including noise—causing poor generalization
to new data. Symptoms include high train accuracy but low validation accuracy.

Example 1.9

User

What is transfer learning?
AI Response

Transfer learning reuses a model trained on one task as a starting point for another related task, reducing
training time and data requirements significantly.

Example 1.10

User

What is data augmentation?
AI Response

Data augmentation artificially increases training data by applying transformations like rotation, cropping, and
flipping to existing samples, improving model generalization.



